<h2 class="mt-6 text-xl font-semibold text-white">100% On-Device Processing</h2>
<p>
  Every utility in the GramSeva Mitra ecosystem — photo compression, PDF editing, resume analysis, and
  document encryption — runs entirely inside your web browser. Processing is delegated to sandboxed
  <strong>Web Workers</strong> so heavy tasks never block the page and never leave your device.
</p>
<p class="mt-3">
  We do <strong>not</strong> upload, store, transmit, or retain your photos, signatures, PDFs, resume
  files, or passwords on our servers. Your documents are never sent to remote APIs for processing. This
  architecture aligns with <strong>GDPR</strong> and <strong>CCPA</strong> principles of data
  minimization and zero cloud retention.
</p>

<h2 class="mt-6 text-xl font-semibold text-white">What We Do Not Collect</h2>
<p>
  We do not maintain user accounts, payment profiles, or usage analytics tied to your identity. We do
  not sell or share personal data with advertisers or data brokers.
</p>

<h2 class="mt-6 text-xl font-semibold text-white">Local App State</h2>
<p>
  Your browser may store lightweight preferences — such as recently selected tools or UI settings — in
  <strong>local storage</strong> on your device only. This cache helps the app remember your last session
  and can be cleared at any time through your browser settings. No document content is written to local
  storage.
</p>

<h2 class="mt-6 text-xl font-semibold text-white">Infrastructure Logs</h2>
<p>
  We do not use third-party tracking cookies. Our CDN provider (Cloudflare) may collect standard
  security and performance logs (IP address, request metadata) independent of your file processing, which
  occurs only on your device.
</p>

<h2 class="mt-6 text-xl font-semibold text-white">Pro Serverless Processing</h2>
<p>
  When GramSeva Mitra Pro features launch, any file you upload for serverless GPU or CPU processing
  (for example, advanced PDF extraction or AI rewriting) is handled in transient memory only. We do
  <strong>not</strong> persist uploaded Pro inputs or generated outputs on our servers after the job
  completes — files are deleted immediately when processing finishes.
</p>

